The paper discusses the construction of zero-difference balanced (ZDB) functions, which have applications in coding theory, cryptography, and communications engineering. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Signal Processing (cs.SI), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories.
